# AgentForge — Cursor project rules
# Route natural-language commands to the universal prompt files.
When the user says "specify"/"specify my agent"  -> read prompts/specify.md and follow it.
When the user says "plan"                          -> read prompts/plan.md and follow it.
When the user says "design"                        -> read prompts/design.md and follow it.
When the user says "validate"                      -> read prompts/validate.md and follow it.
When the user says "tasks"                         -> read prompts/tasks.md and follow it.
When the user says "implement"                     -> read prompts/implement.md and follow it.
  /implement MUST ask the user which ADK auth mechanism to use (Step 1.5) and wait for
  a/b/c/d before generating any code; write APP_DIR/auth-config.yml then app/auth.py.
  After code gen, ask "Do you want basic testing?" — only run import smoke + hooks if yes.
  Always generate APP_DIR/docs/DEPLOYMENT.md and docs/DISASTER-RECOVERY.md (GCloud deploy + DR runbook).
  /implement MUST generate Google ADK agents only (package google-adk, imports from google.adk).
  Follow skills/adk-agents/SKILL.md + memory/adk-reference.md; docs https://adk.dev/llms.txt.
  Never use LangChain/LangGraph/CrewAI/AutoGen or raw LLM SDK chat loops as the agent runtime.
  Tools: FunctionTool by default; MCP only as client to existing remote/public MCP
  (GitHub, GCP MCP, MCP Toolbox for Databases, etc.) — never build custom MCP servers.
Always resolve APP_DIR via prompts/workspace.md first (apps/<slug>/). Never write spec/plan/design/code into the template root.
Always fill APP_DIR/spec.md against templates/spec-template.md (11 sections).
